2. Interpretation
In these Regulations, unless the context otherwise requires—
“citizenship office” means the office of the Chief Passports and Citizenship Officer;
“immigration officer” has the meaning assigned to the term in the Immigration and Deportation Act,
2010;
[Act No. 18 of 2010]
“law enforcement officer” means—
(a) a police officer of or above the rank of inspector;
(b) a passports and citizenship officer; or
(c) an immigration officer;
“residence permit” has the meaning assigned to the term in the Immigration and Deportation Act, 2010;
[Act No. 18 of 2010]
“senior government officer” means a public officer at management level; and
“spouse permit” has the meaning assigned to the term in the Immigration and Deportation Act, 2010.
[Act No. 18 of 2010]

15. Form of registers
The register of—
(a) citizens by registration shall be in Form XIV set out in the First Schedule;
(b) children presumed to be citizens by birth shall be in Form XV set out in the First Schedule;
(c) citizens by adoption shall be in Form XVI set out in the First schedule;
(d) persons who have renounced or been deprived of citizenship shall be in Form XVII set out in the
First Schedule; and
(e) citizens who hold dual citizenship shall be in Form XVIII set out in the First Schedule.
